The paper proposes a head detection model using convolutional neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design choices made for the model, which can be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) aspect. The model is designed for surveillance applications, which can be categorized under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the hardware requirements and runtime of the model, which can be considered as a multimedia (cs.MM) aspect.
